A Christmas Fantasy Parade	
Alice in Wonderland	"Ride vehicles fit 3 adults, or 2 adults and 2 kids. The ride has an outdoor component, but will close when it rains."
Astro Orbitor	Ride vehicles can fit 2 adults or 3 kids. The Astro Orbitor is standard spinner ride. Each rocket is controlled by the riders using a control at the rider's feet.
Autopia	"2 people will fit per vehicle. Riders must be 32 inches to ride, but must be with someone who is at least 54 inches. Riders drive the car, giving kids a taste of getting behind the wheel."
Big Thunder Mountain Railroad	"A fantastic family roller coaster. On many coasters, fans try to sit in either the front of the train, or the back of the train, depending on the experience they want. The special effects for Thunder Mountain are timed for the middle of the train, so don't try to get the first three or last three rows."
Buzz Lightyear Astro Blasters	This shooter dark ride was designed to work with an online computer game. The computer effects now happen in the ride automatically. Blue and purple targets will net you the most points.
Casey Jr. Circus Train	
Chip 'n Dale Treehouse	Chip 'n Dale have left there home open for kids to explore. Their treehouse is FILLED with nuts.
Davy Crockett's Explorer Canoes	The only ride at Disneyland powered by the guests. It gives a good taste of what it's like to take a real canoe trip on the real rivers of America.
Disney and Pixar's Toy Story 4 Sneak Peek	
Disneyland Band at Main Street, U.S.A.	
Disneyland Band at Frontierland	
Disneyland Forever	
Disneyland Monorail	The American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) has declared this ride a historic engineering landmark. It was the first daily-operating monorail in North America.
Disneyland Railroad	"The Disneyland Railroad lets you see everything in the park. It's great for when you want a good overview of the different areas at Disneyland, or if you want something fun to do while you eat a snack."
Disneyland Railroad - Main Street, USA	
